args: O power universal, hear my decree...\nEssence of speed, winds of flight...
(Okay, nice! Today I'll try adding more\nincantations to increase its power.)
Path of heaven, road of clouds...\nAnd clouds of heaven...\nAnd, and...sky of clouds!
Wu Kong! If you chant that much,\nthe relic's power will grow too great!
*sigh* How many times must I tell you\nthat chants need to be limited to\ncorrespond with your own abilities?
What is it, Yulong? Why the hurry?
Master Fa Ming has taken charge\nof the Ling Xuan Dan.
We've not a moment to lose.\nCome with me, Wu Kong.
I've heard tell of this miasma!
Looks like it's coming from that jewel he's\nholding. Lemme just grab tha—
That jewel is the Ling Xuan Dan—a\nterribly dangerous relic that exudes\na most fearsome miasma.
Coming into contact with it brings about\nunimaginable pain. Some even perish\nfrom the agony of it.
We need to take it from him now!
It may be so—but it is a choice\nI make with open eyes.
Master, I cannot believe you've taken up\nthe duty of keeping the Ling Xuan Dan\nunder control...
Duty? What are you talking about?
Even when sealed, the Ling Xuan Dan's\nmiasma never subsides; it continues to\nblanket all around it in a fog of death.
The only way to stave this off is for a\ngreat sealer to control the relic and\nsuppress the miasma.

To that end, great sealers from each era
have looked after the relic in secret,
taking the miasma into their bodies
and quelling its power.
Yes. He will spend hundreds of years\nenduring a pain without end.
Okay, that's insane. There HAS to be a\nway to just stop this poison mist crap!
Qilin legends do speak\nof one possible way...
If we were in possession of this relic's\nopposite—the Su Jindan—we could\nperhaps neutralize the miasma.
Fine then! We go get that relic and—
Alas, the Su Jindan's location has been\nlost to the ravages of time.
Many sealers over the years have searched\nfor it, but none have been successful.
Right now, our only option is for a great\nsealer to use their own life force to\nconstrain the relic's power.
Hmph. Now do you see, boy?\nThis is our resolve as Qilin!
We chose to continue shouldering the\nburden of the dark legacy we have\ninherited from our ancestors.
You do not have such resolve, boy—\nyou could not even ATTEMPT to have it!
You are a mere human with no relation\nwhatsoever to the history of our tribe.
This is hardly the time to bring up\nsuch sensitive matters, master.
No. He's right. I don't have\nthat kind of resolve...
Because I REFUSE to have it!
Just the truth. We can go around and\naround on this point forever, but I'm\nnever going to be a Qilin.
No matter how much I train, I'll never\ntruly understand the weight your tribe\nhas taken on its shoulders.
But I AM a sealer, and that means\nI find and neutralize ancient relics.
And since that's got nothing to do with\nwhether I'm Qilin or human, I'm gonna\ngo out there and find the Su Jindan!
Then your master will be free!
Wu Kung, wait! ...Heavens, but that boy\nis just SO terribly reckless sometimes.
Save your worry—he'll give up and come\ncrawling back before the day is out.
That old goat thinks he's a real hot potato,\nbut all he's doing is getting himself killed!
Just you watch!\nI can't wait to see your face when I show \nup with the Su Jindan!
